I recently moved to this neighborhood n discovered Fine Food Cuisine during our pandemic lockdown. I am a very picky eater with food allergies. I am very careful to order just anywhere. I read all the reviews n they did not disappoint. I mostly order just the chicken sandwich, it comes with fries. It sounds real simple but you’d be surprised how many restaurants can jack up a chicken sandwich. Fine Food Cuisine makes the best. Every time I go the chicken is seasoned well n cooked to perfection. And the bread is always fresh. When you call ahead be patient because they will not always answer on the first try. They stay busy. If you don’t call ahead be prepared to wait about 20 minutes... maybe longer. The food is cooked to order. I’d wait all day for fresh cooked food. If you are used to the finer foods in life you want to experience Fine Food Cuisine. They are black owned n I support their business whenever I don’t feel like cooking. It’s the best food I’ve had in The Bronx.
